  temp_mo[temp_mo==TRUE] <-1

movie_name <- movie$Title
docs <- Corpus(VectorSource(movie_name))
toSpace <- content_transformer(function (x , pattern ) gsub(pattern, " ", x))
docs <- tm_map(docs, toSpace, "/")
docs <- tm_map(docs, toSpace, "@")
docs <- tm_map(docs, toSpace, "\\|")

#### clean names
# Convert the text to lower case
docs <- tm_map(docs, content_transformer(tolower))
# Remove numbers
docs <- tm_map(docs, removeNumbers)
# Remove english common stopwords
docs <- tm_map(docs, removeWords, stopwords("english"))
# Remove your own stop word
# specify your stopwords as a character vector
docs <- tm_map(docs, removeWords, c("blabla1", "blabla2")) 
# Remove punctuations
docs <- tm_map(docs, removePunctuation)
# Eliminate extra white spaces
docs <- tm_map(docs, stripWhitespace)
# Text stemming
# docs <- tm_map(docs, stemDocument)

dtm <- TermDocumentMatrix(docs)
m <- as.matrix(dtm)
v <- sort(rowSums(m),decreasing=TRUE)
d <- data.frame(word = names(v),freq=v)

set.seed(1234)
wordcloud(words = d$word, freq = d$freq, min.freq = 1,
          max.words=200, random.order=FALSE, rot.per=0.35, 
          colors=brewer.pal(8, "Dark2"))

I use method descaussed in https://rpubs.com/vitidN/203264.

er_movie_id = which(is.na(movie$year))
rating = rating %>% filter(! MovieID %in% er_movie_id )
rating <- rating[complete.cases(rating),]
#convert rating-per-row dataframe into sparse User-Item matrix
rating$MovieID = as.factor(rating$MovieID)
rating$UserID = as.factor(rating$UserID)


aggrData <- split(rating$MovieID,rating$UserID)

listData <- list()
for (i in 1:length(aggrData)) {
    listData[[i]] <- as.character(aggrData[[i]][!duplicated(aggrData[[i]])])
}

trnsData <- as(listData,"transactions")

rule_param = list(
    supp = 0.001,
    conf = 0.7,
    maxlen = 2
)
assoc_rules = apriori(trnsData,parameter = rule_param)
## Apriori
## 
## Parameter specification:
##  confidence minval smax arem  aval originalSupport maxtime support minlen
##         0.7    0.1    1 none FALSE            TRUE       5   0.001      1
##  maxlen target   ext
##       2  rules FALSE
## 
## Algorithmic control:
##  filter tree heap memopt load sort verbose
##     0.1 TRUE TRUE  FALSE TRUE    2    TRUE
## 
## Absolute minimum support count: 69 
## 
## set item appearances ...[0 item(s)] done [0.00s].
## set transactions ...[10677 item(s), 69878 transaction(s)] done [1.92s].
## sorting and recoding items ... [6605 item(s)] done [0.35s].
## creating transaction tree ... done [0.07s].
## checking subsets of size 1 2
## Warning in apriori(trnsData, parameter = rule_param): Mining stopped
## (maxlen reached). Only patterns up to a length of 2 returned!
##  done [4.99s].
## writing ... [186918 rule(s)] done [0.16s].
## creating S4 object  ... done [0.04s].
assoc_rules = subset(assoc_rules, lift >= 4.323)
assoc_rules = as(assoc_rules,"data.frame")
rules = sapply(assoc_rules$rules,function(x){
    x = gsub("[\\{\\}]", "", regmatches(x, gregexpr("\\{.*\\}", x))[[1]])
    x = gsub("=>",",",x)
    x = str_replace_all(x," ","")
    return( x )
})

rules = as.character(rules)
rules = str_split(rules,",")

data_rules<- do.call(rbind.data.frame, rules)
colnames(data_rules) <-c('left','right')

for each film in top list I find rules that contain in left of rules. then by finding intercection of all movies that they recommend I find best movies for these 4 movie .i didnt find * No Country for Old Men (2007) in movies so i remove it.

m <- c('Castle in the Sky (Tenk no shiro Rapyuta) (1986)','Cast Away (2000)','No Country for Old Men (2007)','Memento (2000)')
movie %>%  filter (Title %in%m) -> temp
l <- list()
count <- 1
for (id in temp$MovieID){
    data_rules %>% filter(left==id) -> data_temp
    l[[count]] <- data_temp$right
    count <- count + 1
}
